description: Nomao is a dataset for data deduplication of place information. It contains features comparing two places (spots) collected from multiple web sources to determine if they refer to the same physical location. The dataset was enriched during the Nomao Challenge at ECML-PKDD 2012 conference.
source: UCI Machine Learning Repository / Nomao Labs
creator: Laurent Candillier and Vincent Lemaire (Nomao Labs)

feature_categories.name_similarity: Features comparing place names using various string metrics
feature_categories.location_similarity: Features comparing geographic coordinates and locations

labeling_methods.human_prior: First 29,104 instances labeled by human expert
labeling_methods.marg: 917 instances labeled using margin-based active learning

use_case: Identifying duplicate place entries in location-based services, search engines, and business directories. Essential for data quality in mapping applications and local search.
active_learning_context: Dataset was specifically designed for active learning research, demonstrating how to efficiently label data for deduplication tasks
ethical_considerations: Place data may contain business information that could be sensitive. Deduplication accuracy is crucial for fair representation of businesses in search results and maps.
